<DocsLayout title="libstorage API Reference">
  <h1 class="page-title">libstorage C API Reference</h1>
  <p class="page-subtitle">Low-level C interface with stable ABI for language bindings</p>

  <div class="intro-block">
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/logos-storage/logos-storage-nim">libstorage</a> exposes a C binding that serves as
      a stable contract for integrating Logos Storage into other languages. Official bindings are available for
      <a href="https://github.com/logos-storage/logos-storage-go-bindings">Go</a>,
      <a href="https://github.com/logos-storage/logos-storage-rust-bindings">Rust</a>, and
      <a href="https://github.com/logos-storage/easylibstorage">C (easylibstorage)</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The library provides asynchronous operations through worker threads, with results delivered via callbacks.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================================ -->
  <h2 class="section-heading" id="core-types">Core Types</h2>

  <div class="type-def">
    <div class="type-def-header">
      <span class="type-label">Typedef</span>
      <span class="type-name">StorageCallback</span>
    </div>
    <div class="type-def-body">
      <pre>typedef void (*StorageCallback)(int callerRet, const char *msg, size_t len, void *userData);</pre>
      <p class="type-desc">Callback function type used for all asynchronous operations. The <code>callerRet</code> parameter indicates the status of the call using the return codes below.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="type-def">
    <div class="type-def-header">
      <span class="type-label">Enum</span>
      <span class="type-name">Return Codes</span>
    </div>
    <div class="type-def-body">
      <table class="enum-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Code</th><th>Value</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="enum-name">RET_OK</td><td class="enum-value">0</td><td class="enum-desc">Job dispatched successfully.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="enum-name">RET_ERR</td><td class="enum-value">1</td><td class="enum-desc">Immediate failure.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="enum-name">RET_MISSING_CALLBACK</td><td class="enum-value">2</td><td class="enum-desc">Required callback was not provided.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="enum-name">RET_PROGRESS</td><td class="enum-value">3</td><td class="enum-desc">Progress update during an operation.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

